{
  "text": "e mechanism of the mobilization is not yet known. e body likely responds with the release of tocopherol from the liver under conditions of stress. e liver plays an important function in regulation of vitamin E disposition, metabolism, and excretion through \u03b1-TTP [CITATION_1] . Pincemail et al. [CITATION_2] demonstrated that the plasma tocopherol levels increased signicantly in subjects during intensive exercise, which also caused the production of oxidative radicals. e mobilization of tocopherol could help to prevent lipoperoxidation phenomena occurring in skeletal muscle during exercise. e rapid turnover rate of tocopherol in plasma may result in the marked decline of plasma tocopherol concentration. e uctuation in plasma \u03b1-tocopherol levels may demonstrate the animals attempt to address physiological requirements and achieve homeostasis.",
  "correct_citation": {
